      "title": "Isolate the kelvin term",
      "content": "Subtract $32$, then multiply by $\\frac{5}{9}$.<br/>$$732.33=\\frac{9(u-273.15)}{5}$$<br/>$$\\frac{5(732.33)}{9}=u-273.15$$<br/>$$406.85=u-273.15$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add the offset",
      "content": "Add $273.15$ to both sides.<br/>$$u=406.85+273.15=680$$<br/>The answer is <strong>680</strong>."
